The paper discusses the design of a tool that uses natural language processing and knowledge representation and reasoning to convert narratives to an action language system description. This falls under the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also evaluates the effectiveness of the tool in answering questions, which could fall under the sub-categories of cryptography and security (cs.CR) and software engineering (cs.SE).
